f=Engineering/dev/custom/code-review-standards/assets/review-checklist.md · h1:Code Review Checklist dev/code-review-standards=Run order. Scope diff only. Stack-specific lint rules come stack-profile; universal. · h2:Integrity agent-authored code (blocking, before else)=API/method/endpoint/param called actually exists (verified against real dependency, diff's claim), mock, placeholder, fixture data presented wired-up (hardcoded values, example.com, lorem), test weakened, skipped, deleted make gate pass (automatic block pending written justification), TODO NotImplemented empty handler behind "done" "feature complete" claim, Diff touches files stated task requires (over-broad diff finding; Rail 1-adjacent signal) · h2:1. Correctness (load-bearing)=change what claims?, Happy path traced; error paths traced, Edge cases tests don't cover (empty, null, huge, concurrent, malformed), breaking change public contract without migration/version bump, Idempotency retries operation repeated · h2:2. Security (load-bearing)=external input validated sanitized boundary, Authorization checked new path (not authentication), secrets, keys, tokens code logs, Injection surfaces (SQL, command, template, SSRF, XSS) addressed, New external surface auth change **routed aegis before approval** · h2:3. Tests=Non-trivial logic carries tests, Tests assert behavior, execute, quinn's required tiers change type present, Fragile-area diffs (quinn's regression map) carry targeted regression · h2:4. Style=stack-profile conventions followed, Names say what things are; dead code, Readable next person, author · h2:Charter gate (blocking)=Any new external-tool call **plan-locked** (Rail, Any data mutation routes **operator-run script** agent-executed destructive (Rail, Any sandbox-escaping tool use denied (Rail · h2:Charter gate (blocking)=**Verdict:** APPROVE REQUEST CHANGES (each item: `file:line problem fix`)